Chapter 7: Common Operations
Insert
mp[5]=10;

means

Key =5

Value =10
Increase Frequency
mp[5]++;

If

5

doesn't exist,

C++ automatically creates

5->0

then increments

5->1
Find
if(mp.find(5)!=mp.end())

Means

Does key 5 exist?

Shortcut

if(mp.count(5))

Returns

1

if present

0

otherwise.

Erase
mp.erase(5);

Deletes

5
Chapter 8: Pattern Recognition

When should your brain scream

"HASHING!!"

If question says

✅ Count frequency

✅ First unique element

✅ Duplicate element

✅ Contains duplicate

✅ Pair exists

✅ Common elements

✅ Group same values

✅ Count characters

✅ Anagrams

Hashing is probably involved.
